{"TopicId":220616,"ForumId":120,"TopicTitle":"Suggestion: Bring back old trajectory interactivity","CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-03T21:23:09Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-03T21:23:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Screenshot-1.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.postimg.cc/BQRkvS68/Screenshot-1.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe new system (left square) is now used for placing MNs, but I think it makes more sense to do it as KSP 1 did it (putting it on right square). No less guesswork involved on where the MN will land.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DoomsdayDuck555","CreatedById":229813,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-03T21:50:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not both?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-03T21:57:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224336670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221699048203\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229813\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DoomsdayDuck555\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, DoomsdayDuck555 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy not both?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it is an option...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"QwertyHpp","CreatedById":226478,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-04T00:49:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAgreed - although I think this might actually be a bug as it does sometimes appear to work with both, but often the PE node will disappear from the SOE view (right square) and you\u0027ll be unable to place a manoeuvre node - not sure what causes the change in behaviour.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf this is intended behaviour then should def be changed as it also makes it more annoying to fine-tune the approach from afar as you have to go pinpoint the right PE on the main trajectory (left square) and then switch over to see the angle etc.. relative to the planet in the SOE view (right square) while keeping the pinned PE in view\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Emanuel01","CreatedById":219461,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-18T23:30:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this new system is my least favorite feature of the game so far. The concentric effect while entering/exiting \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E are ugly and distracting and the lack of maneuvers or PE indicator is a straight downgrade. This needs a lot of polishing and improvement IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"cocoscacao","CreatedById":225696,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-19T15:36:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224341098\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700350218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Emanuel01\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 hours ago, Emanuel01 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this new system is my least favorite feature of the game so far. The concentric effect while entering/exiting \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E are ugly and distracting and the lack of maneuvers or PE indicator is a straight downgrade. This needs a lot of polishing and improvement IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHopefully with more colors. Just replace circles with entry/exit symbols and paint them blue/red, something.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NaughtyMonster","CreatedById":210559,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-21T13:08:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224341098\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700350218\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022219461\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Emanuel01\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/18/2023 at 11:30 PM, Emanuel01 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think this new system is my least favorite feature of the game so far. The concentric effect while entering/exiting \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESOI\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E are ugly and distracting and the lack of maneuvers or PE indicator is a straight downgrade. This needs a lot of polishing and improvement IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI agree; the concentric blue circles are visually overpowering and distracting. I feel they could be consistently smaller and still indicate that an encounter will occur.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-22T02:05:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224341244\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700408164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cocoscacao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/19/2023 at 10:36 AM, cocoscacao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHopefully with more colors. Just replace circles with entry/exit symbols and paint them blue/red, something.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe I could come up with a drawing of something that would work...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022clIGg5k.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.67\u0022 height=\u0022678\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/clIGg5k.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-22T02:05:26Z\u0022 title=\u002211/22/2023 02:05  AM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 22\u0022\u003ENovember 22, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Superfluous J\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-22T03:36:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224341945\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700618707\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224341244\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700408164\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225696\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022cocoscacao\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/19/2023 at 3:36 PM, cocoscacao said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHopefully with more colors. Just replace circles with entry/exit symbols and paint them blue/red, something.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe I could come up with a drawing of something that would work...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/clIGg5k.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022clIGg5k.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002264.67\u0022 height=\u0022678\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/clIGg5k.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the splashes are way better at communicating that your vessel is going to be under the influence of another gravitational source and that this is determined by their SOIs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe biggest problem people see in it is that the splashes are too big. Can\u0027t they just be turned down instead of removed altogether?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Periple","CreatedById":225622,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-24T12:28:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224341960\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700624161\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/22/2023 at 5:36 AM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe biggest problem people see in it is that the splashes are too big. Can\u0027t they just be turned down instead of removed altogether?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would help a lot if they didn\u0027t scale with zoom and the exit and entry splashes were clearly differentiated visually. My main issue is that they get in the way big time when planning maneuvers in a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESoI\u003C/abbr\u003E I haven\u0027t yet entered, e.g. a Jool gravity capture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NaughtyMonster","CreatedById":210559,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-27T10:22:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224342442\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022220616\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221700828931\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022225622\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Periple\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/24/2023 at 12:28 PM, Periple said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would help a lot if they didn\u0027t scale with zoom\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIndeed. There seems to be a more general issue with the scaling of various GUI components; capsule icons often appear huge and, occasionally, so tiny as to be nearly invisible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}